# WindSpot Environment Variables

# Next.js
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Supabase (for chat feature)
# Get these from your Supabase project dashboard: https://supabase.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here

# Gemini API Key (for news generation)
# Get one free at: https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
GEMINI_API_KEY=your-gemini-api-key-here

# Note: For chat to work, you need to:
# 1. Create a free Supabase account at https://supabase.com
# 2. Create a new project
# 3. Run the SQL in supabase-schema.sql in the SQL Editor
# 4. Copy the URL and anon key to this file (rename to .env.local)
# 5. Get a Gemini API key at https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
# 6. Run: npm run news:generate (uses .env.local for local dev)
